Ban said on Wednesday at a conference that he intends to meet this month with foreign ministers from five permanent countries present at the Council - Russia, China, England and France - on the margins of the ministerial session of the General Assembly to discuss Syria.
Ban expressed regret that the divisions in the Council and between the Syrian people and the regional powers "have made this situation unresolved".
Ban asked the five permanent members to demonstrate solidarity and unity when they were able to conclude an agreement on Iran's nuclear weapons, thus addressing the crisis in Syria.
